  "title": "Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><u>1. </u><u><strong>JOB PURPOSE</strong></u></p><p>The jobholder is responsible for the liaison, coordination and implementation of projects in the Home, assisting the Department to ensure smooth operations.</p><p></p><p><u>2. </u><u><strong>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></u></p><p>2.1 <u>Primary Responsibilities and Duties (80%) Projects</u></p><p>2.1.1 Project management and liaison (Internal & External)</p><p>a. Soft Facilities & Contracts Mgmt</p><p>b. Procurement-related or Information Technology</p><p>c. Innovation & Quality Initiatives</p><p>d. Government submissions or external collaborations</p><p>e. Others (e.g. Logistics)</p><p><br /></p><p>2.1.2 <u>Operations</u></p><p>a. Control and Maintain purchase requisition and order records, assisting to manage procurement process according to finance guidelines and best practice</p><p>b. Support internal programme planning and community operations, including sourcing for sponsors/donors</p><p>c. Tracking of Balance Scorecard KPIs</p><p><br /></p><p>2.1.3 <u>Communications</u></p><p>a. Develop marketing and branding strategies for the Nursing Home</p><p>b. Develop and manage publicity and social media content, and produce necessary</p><p>collaterals</p><p><br /></p><p>2.2 <u>Secondary Responsibilities and duties (20%)</u></p><p>2.2.1 Perform Secretariat duties, including minutes taking, developing, improving and compiling Department SOPs, budget tracking, and maintaining committee records involving Operations Department</p><p>2.2.3 Any other relevant duties as assigned by supervisor</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
